In [5]:
def min_max_scailing(x, max_value = None, min_value = None):
    if max_value is None:
        max_value = x.max()
    if min_value is None:
        min_value = x.min()
    
    return (x - min_value) / (max_value - min_value)

In [181]:
years = 2
In [182]:
for i in range(0, years):
    if i == 0:
        spl_tol = scipy.interpolate.UnivariateSpline(
                                [i for i in range(0, round(len(series) / years))],
                                min_max_scailing(series['totalOrder'][
                                    0 : round(len(series) / years)],
                                                max_value = series['totalOrder'].max(),
                                                min_value = series['totalOrder'].min()),
                                k = 5)
        tol_array = spl_tol([i for i in range(0, round(len(series) / years))])
    else:
        spl_tol = scipy.interpolate.UnivariateSpline(
                        [i for i in range(i * round(len(series) / years),
                                          (i + 1) * round(len(series) / years))],
                        min_max_scailing(series['totalOrder'][
                                    i * round(len(series) / years) :
                                    (i + 1) * round(len(series) / years)],
                                                max_value = series['totalOrder'].max(),
                                                min_value = series['totalOrder'].min()
                        ),
                        k = 5)
        temp = spl_tol([i for i in range(i * round(len(series) / years),
                                          (i + 1) * round(len(series) / years))])
        
        tol_array = np.concatenate([tol_array, temp])

def min_max_scailing(x, max_value = None, min_value = None):
    if max_value is None:
        max_value = x.max()
    if min_value is None:
        min_value = x.min()
    
    return (x - min_value) / (max_value - min_value)
In [11]:
dataframe_orderseries['date'] = dataframe_orderseries['createdAt'].astype('datetime64').dt.date

dataframe_orderseries_country = dataframe_orderseries.copy()

dataframe_orderseries_country['isKR'] = dataframe_orderseries_country['countryCode'] == 'KR'

dataframe_orderseries_country = dataframe_orderseries_country.groupby(['date','isKR'])['initTotalKRW'].sum()

dataframe_orderseries_country = dataframe_orderseries_country.reset_index()

years = 2

kr_total = dataframe_orderseries_country[dataframe_orderseries_country['isKR']]['initTotalKRW'].reset_index(drop = True)
foreign_total = dataframe_orderseries_country[dataframe_orderseries_country['isKR'] == False]['initTotalKRW'].reset_index(drop = True)
In [26]:
for i in range(0, years):
    if i == 0:
        spl_sku = scipy.interpolate.UnivariateSpline(
                                [i for i in range(0, round(len(kr_total) / years))],
                                min_max_scailing(kr_total[
                                    0 : round(len(kr_total) / years)],
                                                max_value = kr_total.max(),
                                                min_value = kr_total.min()),
                                k = 5)
        sku_array = spl_sku([i for i in range(0, round(len(kr_total) / years))])
    else:
        spl_sku = scipy.interpolate.UnivariateSpline(
                        [i for i in range(i * round(len(kr_total) / years),
                                          (i + 1) * round(len(kr_total) / years) - 1)],
                        min_max_scailing(kr_total[
                                    i * round(len(kr_total) / years) :
                                    (i + 1) * round(len(kr_total) / years)],
                                                max_value = kr_total.max(),
                                                min_value = kr_total.min()
                        ),
                        k = 5)
        temp = spl_sku([i for i in range(i * round(len(kr_total) / years),
                                          (i + 1) * round(len(kr_total) / years))])
        
        sku_array = np.concatenate([sku_array, temp])
